            {# EN Founder #}
            <div class="lang-content lang-en active">
                <h1>The Founder’s Story</h1>
                <p>Hello! I’m <strong>Master Manikant</strong>, and I created EnglishVidya to help students who struggle with English — just like I once did.</p>
                <blockquote style="border-left: 4px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 15px; margin-left: 0; font-style: italic; color: var(--text-secondary); background: var(--bg-hover); padding: 15px; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;">
                    “मैंने अंग्रेजी सीखने और समझने में बहुत मुश्किलों का सामना किया, और मैं नहीं चाहता कि किसी और को भी ये कठिनाइयाँ झेलनी पड़े।”<br>
                    <span style="font-size: 0.9em;">(I faced many difficulties in learning and understanding English, and I don't want anyone else to go through those same hardships.)</span>
                </blockquote>
                <p>My educational background includes a <strong>B.Sc. in Mathematics, a B.Ed. degree, and STET qualification</strong>. Over the years, I have taught students ranging from Classes 6 to 10 in coaching institutes, and Class 12 students through home tuition.</p>

                <h2>The Incident That Changed Everything</h2>
                <p>The story of EnglishVidya didn't start in a boardroom; it started in a classroom.</p>
                <p>One day, while teaching a Class 10 student, I asked him to translate a very simple Hindi sentence into English. Despite studying English for years in school, reading grammar books, and attending coaching classes, <strong>he went completely blank</strong>. He couldn't do it.</p>
                <p>That moment hit me hard. Millions of Hindi-medium students study English merely to "pass the exam." They memorize rules, cram definitions, and yet, they live in constant fear of speaking or writing practical English. I decided it was time to build a platform that solves this exact problem so nobody has to go through the same confusion and frustration.</p>

                <h2>Rebuilding from Zero</h2>
                <p>The journey of building EnglishVidya was not easy. I purchased the domain and hosting on <strong>18 March 2025</strong>. For months, I poured my heart into it, and by <strong>January 2026</strong>, the website was running smoothly with great content.</p>
                <p>However, due to financial struggles, the hosting expired on <strong>18 March 2026</strong>. I couldn't renew it. I managed to save all the website's data and hard work on my old laptop, hoping to upload it later when things got better.</p>
                <p>But fate had other plans. In <strong>June 2026</strong>, my old laptop completely broke down and could not be repaired. Years of hard work, drafted articles, and data were trapped inside a dead machine. I had nothing left.</p>
                <p>It was devastating. But a mission driven by true purpose doesn't die. Instead of giving up, I chose to start from absolute zero. I am rebuilding EnglishVidya from the ground up—this time, not just as a blog, but as an indestructible, 100% comprehensive learning ecosystem.</p>
            </div>

